embed.description: Numeral or number prefixes are prefixes derived from numerals or occasionally other numbers. In English and other European languages, they are used to coin numerous series of words, such as unicycle - bicycle - tricycle, dyad - triad - decade, biped - quadruped, September - October - November - December, decimal - hexadecimal, sexagenarian - octogenarian, centipede - millipede, etc.
